OL,4,C'accidentally started by one of the
OL,5,Cyoungsters'
OL,7,FWhen firefighters arrived shortly
OL,8,Fafterwards they "put their own lives
OL,9,Fat risk" and "disregarded protocol" in
OL,10,Fan effort to rescue the two children.
OL,12,FHowever, by the time they were pulled
OL,13,Fout of the house, both had suffered an
OL,14,F"unsurvivable" brain injury.
OL,16,FDr Adam Nicholls, a consultant in
OL,17,FPaediatric Intensive Care Medicine at
OL,18,FManchester University NHS Foundation
OL,19,FTrust, told the inquest that by the
OL,20,Ftime the children were rescued from
OL,21,Fthe house "the damage had been done".
OL,1,W~k4j5 hw1~k4~c1 hw}h7}j7}      G5/11
