OL,3,CFire that killed two children
OL,4,C'accidentally started by one of the
OL,5,Cyoungsters'
OL,7,F"The response from the fire and rescue
OL,8,Fservice was incredibly swift. Had it
OL,9,Fnot been for the bravery and courage
OL,10,Fof the firefighters who attended and
OL,11,Fwho put their lives at risk it is
OL,12,Flikely that the children would not
OL,13,Fhave been rescued when they were."
OL,15,F"I have not found the fault of any
OL,16,Findividual or organisation has
OL,17,Fcontributed to the deaths in any way.
OL,18,FWhat occurred was a tragic and
OL,19,Fdevastating accident."
OL,1,W~k4j5 hw1~k4~c1 hw}h7}j7}      G8/11
