OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax     F394A1733271031
OL,3,CFire that killed two children
OL,4,C'accidentally started by one of the
OL,5,Cyoungsters'
OL,7,F"Experience is, of course, how we
OL,8,Flearn. Here the children had been
OL,9,Fwarned about playing with lighters
OL,10,Fbut, I repeat, children experiment,
OL,11,Fand given the evidence I have outlined
OL,12,FI am satisfied that the fire was
OL,13,Fstarted by one of the children with
OL,14,Fthe lighter.
OL,16,F"There is however no evidence
OL,17,Fwhatsoever that this was done
OL,18,Fintentionally to set fire to the
OL,19,Fhouse. They did not appreciate the
OL,20,Frisk that the sofa could catch fire in
OL,21,Fthe way that it did.
OL,1,W~k4j5 hw1~k4~c1 hw}h7}j7}     G10/11
